### Racial Feats

#### [Draconic Aura]
*Prerequisite: Dracthyr*

[Benefit in an AoE around you when in Visage form. Based on the WoW dracthyr's Visage racial ability that increases out of combat health regeneration.]

#### Draconic Breath
*Prerequisite: Dracthyr*

You are able to utilize the breath attack of the dragonflights. At the end of each long rest, you can choose a single dragonflight's breath to imitate: black, blue, bronze, green, or red.

When you take the Attack action, you can replace one of your attacks with a blast of elemental energy, unleashing it in 15-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes 1d10 damage on a failed save, and half as much damage on a successful one. This damage increases by 1d10 when you reach 5th level (2d10), 11th level (3d10), and 17th level (4d10).

The form of the breath attack and the damage type it deals depends on which dragonflight you are imitating, as seen on the Dragon Breath Types table. You can use your Breath Weapon a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.

##### Draconic Breath Types
Dragonflight    | Breath Weapon | Damage Type
----------------|---------------|-------------
Black   | Shadowy fire          | Necrotic
Blue    | Icy magic             | Cold
Bronze  | Static-filled sand    | Lightning
Green   | Green energy          | Acid
Red     | Glowing fire          | Fire

#### Draconic Combat
*Prerequisite: Dracthyr*

You have learned to better utilize your other limbs in combat. When you take the Attack action, you can replace one of your attacks with one of the following:
- You beat your wings fiercely, creating a gust of wind in front of you. Each creature in a 15-foot cone must make a Strength saving throw.
- You whip your tail in a quick swipe low to the ground, potentially knocking down enemies. Each creature within 5 feet of you must make a Dexterity saving throw or be knocked prone. 

#### Draconic Fear
*Prerequisite: Dracthyr*

When angered, you radiate menace. You gain the following benefits:
- Increase your Strength, Constitution, or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- You can roar, forcing each creature of your choice within 30 feet of you to make a Wisdom saving throw (DC 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier). A target automatically succeeds on the save if it can’t hear or see you. On a failed save, a target becomes frightened for 1 minute. If the frightened target takes any damage, it can repeat the saving throw, ending the effect on itself on a success. You can use this trait a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.

#### Draconic Flight
*Prerequisite: Dracthyr, 4th level or higher*

You can now fly using your wings while wearing heavy armor. If you aren't wearing heavy armor, your flying speed increases by 30 feet.

#### [Draconic Magic]
*Prerequisite: Dracthyr*

[Gives some basic low-level spellcasting.]

#### [Draconic Resistance]
*Prerequisite: Dracthyr*

[Gain a switchable resistance to acid, cold, fire, lightning, or necrotic damage. Matches whatever breath attack you took for Draconic Breath.]

#### [Draconic Senses]
*Prerequisite: Dracthyr*

[Blindsight, keen senses. See Awakened dracthyr ability.]

#### [Mechanized Innards]
*Prerequisite: Mechagnome or Gnome (mechagon)*

[Choose X of the following benefits. Can take this feat multiple times.]
- Database Access: Advantage on Intelligence checks
- Electric Web: Can unleash lightning attack
- Frickin Laser Beams: 
- H.O.L.O.: Mirror image
- Jetpack: Fly speed
- Overclock: Take extra action?
- X-Ray Vision

**Combat Analysis.** When you make an attack roll and miss, you can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to your next attack roll against the same target.

**Emergency Failsafe.** You can use your action to roll a number of d4s equal to your proficiency bonus. You regain a number of hit points equal to the number rolled + your Constitution modifier. You can also use this feature at the beginning of your turn if you are unconscious (no action required). Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.

**Grappling Appendages.** You graft two mechanical appendages to your body, such as secondary arms or tentacles. They have a reach of 5 feet, and can lift a number of pounds equal to five times your Strength score. You can use them to do the following simple tasks: lift, drop, hold, push, or pull an object or a creature; open or close a door or a container; grapple someone; or make an unarmed strike. Your GM might allow other simple tasks to be added to that list of options. They can't wield weapons or shields or do anything that requires manual precision, such as using tools or magic items or performing the somatic components of a spell.

**Integrated Database.** You have surgically integrated a database of knowledge into your brain. You gain proficiency in two of the following skills of your choice: Arcana, History, Investigation, Medicine, Nature, or Religion.

