## High Arakkoa

*“Shadows gather when the raven swallows the day. Burning sky is extinguished as black wings fold gently about the heavens. Rest, my children, rest. For even <br /> the sun must sleep.”* <div style="text-align:Right"> 

*— Rukhmar's lullaby, sung by her to the first arakkoa* </div>

### High Arakkoa Traits
Your high arakkoa has the following traits.

***Ability Score Increase.*** Your Intelligence score increases by 2 and your Dexterity score increases by 1.

***Age.*** High arakkoa reach adulthood at age 8 and rarely live longer than 60 years.

***Alignment.*** High arakkoa follow a rigid caste system and set of laws, and most possess a lawful alignment.

***Size.*** High arakkoa are about 7 feet tall and weigh about 160 pounds. Your size is Medium. To set your height and weight randomly, start with rolling the size modifier:

<div style="margin-top: -18px; font-family: ScalySans, sans-serif">

<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ***Size Modifier:*** 2d6
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ***Height:*** 6 feet + 5 inches + your size modifier in inches
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ***Weight in Pounds:*** 125 + (2d4 x your size modifier)

</div>

<div style='margin-top:-3px;'></div>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ***Speed.*** Your base walking speed is 30 feet.

\columnbreak

<div style='margin-top:510px;'></div>

***Flight.*** You have a flying speed of 60 feet. In order to use this ability, you must be unencumbered, not wearing medium or heavy armor, and your hands must be free (not wielding or holding any objects). Your talons are strong enough to grasp and hold items while flying, but you cannot wield weapons in them.

***Talons.*** Your hands and feet possess sharp talons, which you can use to make unarmed attacks. If you hit with them, you deal slashing damage equal to 1d4 + your Dexterity modifier. You can make attacks with your taloned feet while flying.

***Sunlight Dependency.*** The high arakkoa make such heavy use of harnessed sunlight that they have lost much of their nightvision. You have disadvantage on attack rolls and on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on sight when you, the target of your attack, or whatever you are trying to perceive are in dim light.

***Languages.*** You can speak, read, and write Common and Ravenspeech. Ravenspeech sounds like the rough caws of ravens and crows and is difficult to speak by other races. Its writing system looks similar to angular scratches from claws or talons.

***Caste.*** Arakkoa society is divided into strict castes, separated even before they receive a name. Some of these are the laborer, priest, and warrior castes. Choose one of these castes.

#### Laborer Caste

<img src='https://www.gmbinder.com/images/kdufXq1.jpg' style='position:absolute; top:0px; left:0px; width:835px' />
<img src='https://www.gmbinder.com/images/76ytPWI.png' style='position:absolute; bottom:30px; left:0px; width:860px' />
<img src='https://wow.zamimg.com/modelviewer/live/webthumbs/npc/24/57112.png' style='position:absolute; top:190px; left:-60px; width:450px; transform:scaleX(-1);' />

\pagebreak

#### Priest Caste

***Sun Magic.*** You know the *light* cantrip. When you reach 3rd level, you can cast *color spray* once, and it recharges after a long rest. When you reach 5th level, you can cast *scorching ray* once, and it recharges after a long rest. Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for these spells.

#### Warrior Caste
***Keen Sight.*** Long hours of patrolling in the sky has sharpened your visual acuity. You have advantage on Wisdom (Perception) rolls that rely on sight.

